# Trading analysis domain

## Data sources

| Data | Source | Path |
|------|--------|------|
| Account, positions, orders, candles, funding | Bitunix REST + WS | `/bitunix/*`, `wss://fapi.bitunix.com` |
| Deep order book, OI, long/short, taker, klines | Binance REST + WS | `/binance/*`, `wss://fstream.binance.com` |

Symbols are USD-M perpetuals (e.g. `BTCUSDT`). Bitunix and Binance symbols generally match.

## Setup engine (`src/features/analysis/setup/`)

Modular pipeline — keep concerns separated:

- `signal.ts` — candle factors, regime detection, HTF confirmation
- `patterns.ts` — candlestick pattern detection
- `entryQuality.ts` — entry timing/quality scoring
- `reversalRisk.ts` — adverse reversal risk by side
- `backtest.ts` / `rangeBacktest.ts` — historical signal validation
- `straddle.ts` — range-bound dual-leg planning
- `config.ts` — weights, thresholds, HTF settings (single source of truth)
- `engine.ts` — orchestrates modules into `SetupResult` / `TradePlan`
- `order.ts` — order placement helpers (respects `liveTradingEnabled`)

When tuning signals, change `config.ts` constants — don't scatter magic numbers.

## Statistics (`src/features/stats/`)

- `compute.ts` — closed-position analytics (win rate, PF, drawdown, heatmaps)
- `positions.ts` — open position helpers, TP/SL projection
- `review.ts` / `usePositionReviews.ts` — advisory close suggestions on market reversal
- `stopSuggest.ts` — tighten-stop recommendations

Reviews are **advisory only** — never auto-close positions.

## Order ticket safety

- `liveTradingEnabled` must be `true` for real order submission.
- Straddle and single-leg flows go through confirm modals.
- Hedge mode is set before opening positions (Multi-Trade prerequisite).

## Indicators

Core indicators in `src/lib/indicators.ts`: EMA, Bollinger, VWAP, RSI, MACD, Stochastic-RSI, ATR.
Use ATR-normalized distances where the codebase already does (signal factors, stop placement).

## Limitations to preserve in UI copy

- Binance liquidation map is **live-only** (no historical REST).
- OI / long-short / taker data covers ~30 days.
- Binance geo-restrictions show a notice; don't treat as a code bug.
